  "overview_metadata": {
    "overview_number": 2,
    "overview_title": "Slides, Flips, and Spins",
    "overview_subtitle": "Introduction to Rigid Motion",
    "overview_description": "In this lesson, students formalize their understanding of rigid motions using the terms pre-image, image, translation, reflection, line of reflection, rotation, center of rotation, and angle of rotation. They investigate the properties of each transformation. Students recognize that rigid motions preserve the original figure's size and shape, and that translations and rotations also preserve the figure's orientation."
  },
